{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":253,"text":"I am a cultural omnivore,"},{"time":2207,"text":"one whose daily commute is made possible\nby attachment to an iPod --"},{"time":6867,"text":"an iPod that contains Wagner and Mozart,"},{"time":9120,"text":"pop diva Christina Aguilera,"},{"time":11160,"text":"country singer Josh Turner,"},{"time":12800,"text":"gangsta rap artist Kirk Franklin,"},{"time":15259,"text":"concerti, symphonies and more and more."},{"time":17656,"text":"I'm a voracious reader,"},{"time":19194,"text":"a reader who deals with Ian McEwan\ndown to Stephanie Meyer."},{"time":22149,"text":"I have read the Twilight tetralogy."},{"time":25378,"text":"And one who lives for my home theater,"},{"time":27820,"text":"a home theater where I devour\nDVDs, video on demand"},{"time":30823,"text":"and a lot of television."},{"time":32237,"text":"For me, \"Law &amp; Order: SVU,\"\nTina Fey and \"30 Rock\""},{"time":35642,"text":"and \"Judge Judy\" --"},{"time":37238,"text":"\"The people are real, the cases are real,\nthe rulings are final.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":40659,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":41695,"text":"Now, I'm convinced a lot of you\nprobably share my passions,"},{"time":45000,"text":"especially my passion for \"Judge Judy,\""},{"time":47311,"text":"and you'd fight anybody\nwho attempted to take her away from us,"},{"time":50825,"text":"but I'm a little less convinced that you\nshare the central passion of my life,"},{"time":54589,"text":"a passion for the live\nprofessional performing arts,"},{"time":57326,"text":"performing arts that represent\nthe orchestral repertoire, yes,"},{"time":60332,"text":"but jazz as well, modern dance, opera,"},{"time":63000,"text":"theater and more and more and more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65848,"text":"Frankly, it's a sector that many of us\nwho work in the field"},{"time":69000,"text":"worry is being endangered\nand possibly dismantled by technology."},{"time":72749,"text":"While we initially heralded the Internet\nas the fantastic new marketing device"},{"time":77163,"text":"that was going to solve all our problems,"},{"time":79406,"text":"we now realize that the Internet\nis, if anything,"},{"time":81827,"text":"too effective in that regard."},{"time":83470,"text":"Depending on who you read,\nan arts organization"},{"time":86000,"text":"or an artist, who tries\nto attract the attention"},{"time":88490,"text":"of a potential single ticket buyer,"},{"time":90735,"text":"now competes with between three and 5,000\ndifferent marketing messages"},{"time":96000,"text":"a typical citizen sees every single day."},{"time":99260,"text":"We now know, in fact,"},{"time":101001,"text":"that technology is our biggest\ncompetitor for leisure time."},{"time":103792,"text":"Five years ago,"},{"time":105067,"text":"Gen Xers spent 20.7 hours online and TV,\nthe majority on TV."},{"time":109800,"text":"Gen Yers spent even more --"},{"time":111659,"text":"23.8 hours, the majority online."},{"time":114626,"text":"And now, a typical university-entering\nstudent arrives at college"},{"time":120285,"text":"already having spent 20,000 hours online"},{"time":124620,"text":"and an additional 10,000 hours\nplaying video games --"},{"time":128456,"text":"a stark reminder that we operate\nin a cultural context"},{"time":131698,"text":"where video games now outsell\nmusic and movie recordings combined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137905,"text":"Moreover, we're afraid that technology"},{"time":140684,"text":"has altered our very assumptions\nof cultural consumption."},{"time":143747,"text":"Thanks to the Internet,"},{"time":144935,"text":"we believe we can get anything\nwe want whenever we want it,"},{"time":147933,"text":"delivered to our own doorstep."},{"time":149776,"text":"We can shop at three in the morning\nor eight at night,"},{"time":152344,"text":"ordering jeans tailor-made\nfor our unique body types."},{"time":155301,"text":"Expectations of personalization\nand customization"},{"time":159251,"text":"that the live performing arts --"},{"time":161124,"text":"which have set curtain times, set venues,"},{"time":164000,"text":"attendant inconveniences\nof travel, parking and the like --"},{"time":167398,"text":"simply cannot meet."},{"time":169625,"text":"And we're all acutely aware:"},{"time":171290,"text":"what's it going to mean in the future"},{"time":173109,"text":"when we ask someone\nto pay a hundred dollars"},{"time":175309,"text":"for a symphony, opera or ballet ticket,"},{"time":177801,"text":"when that cultural consumer\nis used to downloading on the internet"},{"time":181137,"text":"24 hours a day\nfor 99 cents a song or for free?"},{"time":187402,"text":"These are enormous questions\nfor those of us that work in this terrain."},{"time":191465,"text":"But as particular as they feel to us,\nwe know we're not alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195157,"text":"All of us are engaged"},{"time":196555,"text":"in a seismic, fundamental realignment\nof culture and communications,"},{"time":201243,"text":"a realignment that is shaking\nand decimating the newspaper industry,"},{"time":205031,"text":"the magazine industry,\nthe book and publishing industry and more."},{"time":209710,"text":"Saddled in the performing arts as we are,\nby antiquated union agreements"},{"time":213596,"text":"that inhibit and often prohibit\nmechanical reproduction and streaming,"},{"time":218608,"text":"locked into large facilities\nthat were designed to ossify"},{"time":222476,"text":"the ideal relationship\nbetween artist and audience"},{"time":225847,"text":"most appropriate to the 19th century"},{"time":228156,"text":"and locked into a business model\ndependent on high ticket revenues,"},{"time":231357,"text":"where we charge exorbitant prices."},{"time":233837,"text":"Many of us shudder in the wake\nof the collapse of Tower Records"},{"time":237266,"text":"and ask ourselves, \"Are we next?\""},{"time":241134,"text":"Everyone I talk to in performing arts\nresonates to the words of Adrienne Rich,"},{"time":246000,"text":"who, in \"Dreams of a Common\nLanguage,\" wrote,"},{"time":248198,"text":"\"We are out in a country\nthat has no language, no laws."},{"time":251910,"text":"Whatever we do together is pure invention."},{"time":254472,"text":"The maps they gave us\nare out of date by years.\""},{"time":260204,"text":"And for those of you who love the arts,"},{"time":262133,"text":"aren't you glad you invited\nme here to brighten your day?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":265000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":267000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":268466,"text":"Now, rather than saying that we're\non the brink of our own annihilation,"},{"time":272000,"text":"I prefer to believe that we are engaged\nin a fundamental reformation,"},{"time":275670,"text":"a reformation like the religious\nReformation of the 16th century."},{"time":279906,"text":"The arts reformation,\nlike the religious Reformation,"},{"time":283000,"text":"is spurred in part by technology,"},{"time":284674,"text":"with indeed, the printing press\nreally leading the charge"},{"time":287435,"text":"on the religious Reformation."},{"time":289286,"text":"Both reformations were predicated\non fractious discussion,"},{"time":292361,"text":"internal self-doubt"},{"time":293794,"text":"and massive realignment\nof antiquated business models."},{"time":297846,"text":"And at heart, both reformations, I think,\nwere asking the questions:"},{"time":301256,"text":"who's entitled to practice?"},{"time":303000,"text":"How are they entitled to practice?"},{"time":304730,"text":"And indeed, do we need anyone\nto intermediate for us"},{"time":308742,"text":"in order to have an experience\nwith a spiritual divine?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":313835,"text":"Chris Anderson,\nsomeone I trust you all know,"},{"time":316561,"text":"editor in chief of Wired magazine\nand author of The Long Tail,"},{"time":319597,"text":"really was the first, for me,\nto nail a lot of this."},{"time":322725,"text":"He wrote a long time ago, you know,"},{"time":324420,"text":"thanks to the invention of the Internet,\nweb technology, minicams and more,"},{"time":329969,"text":"the means of artistic production\nhave been democratized"},{"time":333448,"text":"for the first time\nin all of human history."},{"time":337223,"text":"In the 1930s, if any of you wanted\nto make a movie,"},{"time":339700,"text":"you had to work for\nWarner Brothers or RKO,"},{"time":342000,"text":"because who could afford a movie set"},{"time":344000,"text":"and lighting equipment\nand editing equipment"},{"time":346120,"text":"and scoring, and more?"},{"time":347927,"text":"And now who in this room\ndoesn't know a 14 year-old"},{"time":351130,"text":"hard at work on her second,\nthird, or fourth movie?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":353685,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":355504,"text":"Similarly, the means\nof artistic distribution"},{"time":358612,"text":"have been democratized\nfor the first time in human history."},{"time":361417,"text":"Again, in the '30s, Warner Brothers,\nRKO did that for you."},{"time":364392,"text":"Now, go to YouTube, Facebook;"},{"time":366456,"text":"you have worldwide distribution"},{"time":368404,"text":"without leaving the privacy\nof your own bedroom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371954,"text":"This double impact is occasioning"},{"time":374354,"text":"a massive redefinition\nof the cultural market,"},{"time":377366,"text":"a time when anyone is a potential author."},{"time":381282,"text":"Frankly, what we're seeing now\nin this environment"},{"time":383653,"text":"is a massive time,\nwhen the entire world is changing"},{"time":386777,"text":"as we move from a time\nwhen audience numbers are plummeting."},{"time":389939,"text":"But the number of arts participants,"},{"time":392377,"text":"people who write poetry, who sing songs,\nwho perform in church choirs,"},{"time":396214,"text":"is exploding beyond\nour wildest imaginations."},{"time":400320,"text":"This group, others have\ncalled the pro-ams,"},{"time":402837,"text":"amateur artists doing work\nat a professional level."},{"time":405758,"text":"You see them on YouTube,\nin dance competitions,"},{"time":407975,"text":"film festivals and more."},{"time":409682,"text":"They are radically expanding"},{"time":411621,"text":"our notions of the potential\nof an aesthetic vocabulary,"},{"time":414824,"text":"while they are challenging and undermining"},{"time":417000,"text":"the cultural autonomy\nof our traditional institutions."},{"time":420437,"text":"Ultimately, we now live in a world\ndefined not by consumption,"},{"time":424301,"text":"but by participation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427297,"text":"But I want to be clear,"},{"time":429088,"text":"just as the religious Reformation\ndid not spell the end"},{"time":431892,"text":"to the formal Church or to the priesthood;"},{"time":433929,"text":"I believe that our artistic institutions\nwill continue to have importance."},{"time":438137,"text":"They currently are the best opportunities"},{"time":440339,"text":"for artists to have lives\nof economic dignity --"},{"time":442639,"text":"not opulence, of dignity."},{"time":444848,"text":"And they are the places where artists"},{"time":446654,"text":"who deserve and want to work\nat a certain scale of resources"},{"time":449498,"text":"will find a home."},{"time":451583,"text":"But to view them as synonymous\nwith the entirety of the arts community"},{"time":455736,"text":"is, by far, too shortsighted."},{"time":458462,"text":"And indeed, while we've tended to polarize\nthe amateur from the professional,"},{"time":462196,"text":"the single most exciting development\nin the last five to 10 years"},{"time":466450,"text":"has been the rise\nof the professional hybrid artist,"},{"time":470277,"text":"the professional artist who works,"},{"time":471931,"text":"not primarily in the concert hall\nor on the stage;"},{"time":474676,"text":"but most frequently around\nwomen's rights, or human rights,"},{"time":478000,"text":"or on global warming issues\nor AIDS relief for more --"},{"time":480921,"text":"not out of economic necessity,"},{"time":483075,"text":"but out of a deep, organic conviction"},{"time":485653,"text":"that the work that she or he\nis called to do"},{"time":488169,"text":"cannot be accomplished in the traditional\nhermetic arts environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492734,"text":"Today's dance world is not defined solely"},{"time":495229,"text":"by the Royal Winnipeg Ballet\nor the National Ballet of Canada,"},{"time":498442,"text":"but by Liz Lerman's Dance Exchange --"},{"time":500912,"text":"a multi-generational,\nprofessional dance company,"},{"time":504000,"text":"whose dancers range in age from 18 to 82,"},{"time":507632,"text":"and who work with genomic scientists\nto embody the DNA strand"},{"time":511242,"text":"and with nuclear physicists at CERN."},{"time":514178,"text":"Today's professional theater community"},{"time":516334,"text":"is defined, not only the Shaw\nand Stratford Festivals,"},{"time":519623,"text":"but by the Cornerstone Theater\nof Los Angeles --"},{"time":522191,"text":"a collective of artists that after 9/11,"},{"time":525000,"text":"brought together 10 different\nreligious communities --"},{"time":528511,"text":"the Baha'i, the Catholic,"},{"time":530323,"text":"the Muslim, the Jewish,"},{"time":532000,"text":"even the Native American"},{"time":533752,"text":"and the gay and lesbian\ncommunities of faith,"},{"time":535949,"text":"helping them create\ntheir own individual plays"},{"time":539000,"text":"and one massive play,"},{"time":541000,"text":"where they explored\nthe differences in their faith"},{"time":543654,"text":"and found commonality"},{"time":545000,"text":"as an important first step\ntoward cross-community healing."},{"time":549838,"text":"Today's performers, like Rhodessa Jones,\nwork in women's prisons,"},{"time":553374,"text":"helping women prisoners\narticulate the pain of incarceration,"},{"time":556910,"text":"while today's playwrights\nand directors work with youth gangs"},{"time":559832,"text":"to find alternate channels to violence\nand more and more and more."},{"time":565358,"text":"And indeed, I think,\nrather than being annihilated,"},{"time":568000,"text":"the performing arts\nare poised on the brink of a time"},{"time":570502,"text":"when we will be more important\nthan we have ever been."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574441,"text":"You know, we've said for a long time,"},{"time":576228,"text":"we are critical to the health\nof the economic communities in your town."},{"time":579592,"text":"And absolutely --"},{"time":580775,"text":"I hope you know that every dollar spent\non a performing arts ticket in a community"},{"time":584762,"text":"generates five to seven\nadditional dollars for the local economy,"},{"time":587884,"text":"dollars spent in restaurants\nor on parking,"},{"time":589926,"text":"at the fabric stores\nwhere we buy fabric for costumes,"},{"time":592498,"text":"the piano tuner who tunes\nthe instruments, and more."},{"time":595785,"text":"But the arts are going to be more\nimportant to economies as we go forward,"},{"time":599641,"text":"especially in industries\nwe can't even imagine yet,"},{"time":602166,"text":"just as they have been central to the iPod\nand the computer game industries,"},{"time":606126,"text":"which few, if any of us,\ncould have foreseen 10 to 15 years ago."},{"time":610830,"text":"Business leadership will depend\nmore and more on emotional intelligence,"},{"time":615176,"text":"the ability to listen deeply,"},{"time":617165,"text":"to have empathy,"},{"time":618672,"text":"to articulate change,\nto motivate others --"},{"time":621408,"text":"the very capacities that the arts\ncultivate with every encounter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626148,"text":"Especially now,"},{"time":628523,"text":"as we all must confront\nthe fallacy of a market-only orientation,"},{"time":633077,"text":"uninformed by social conscience;"},{"time":635448,"text":"we must seize and celebrate\nthe power of the arts"},{"time":638277,"text":"to shape our individual\nand national characters,"},{"time":640861,"text":"and especially characters\nof the young people,"},{"time":643952,"text":"who all too often are subjected\nto bombardment of sensation,"},{"time":647000,"text":"rather than digested experience."},{"time":650246,"text":"Ultimately, especially now in this world,"},{"time":653262,"text":"where we live in a context of regressive\nand onerous immigration laws,"},{"time":657907,"text":"in reality TV that thrives on humiliation,"},{"time":661270,"text":"and in a context of analysis,"},{"time":663000,"text":"where the thing we hear most repeatedly,\nday in, day out in the United States,"},{"time":667702,"text":"in every train station, every bus station,\nevery plane station is,"},{"time":670831,"text":"\"Ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":672118,"text":"please report any suspicious behavior\nor suspicious individuals"},{"time":676172,"text":"to the authorities nearest to you,\""},{"time":678158,"text":"when all of these ways we are encouraged"},{"time":680120,"text":"to view our fellow human being\nwith hostility and fear"},{"time":683192,"text":"and contempt and suspicion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685916,"text":"The arts, whatever they do,\nwhenever they call us together,"},{"time":688783,"text":"invite us to look at our fellow\nhuman being with generosity and curiosity."},{"time":695210,"text":"God knows, if we ever needed\nthat capacity in human history,"},{"time":699445,"text":"we need it now."},{"time":705114,"text":"You know, we're bound together,"},{"time":707000,"text":"not, I think by technology,\nentertainment and design,"},{"time":710451,"text":"but by common cause."},{"time":712521,"text":"We work to promote\nhealthy vibrant societies,"},{"time":715828,"text":"to ameliorate human suffering,"},{"time":718293,"text":"to promote a more thoughtful,\nsubstantive, empathic world order."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724871,"text":"I salute all of you\nas activists in that quest"},{"time":727475,"text":"and urge you to embrace\nand hold dear the arts in your work,"},{"time":730667,"text":"whatever your purpose may be."},{"time":733346,"text":"I promise you the hand\nof the Doris Duke Charitable Foundation"},{"time":736289,"text":"is stretched out in friendship\nfor now and years to come."},{"time":739012,"text":"And I thank you for your kindness\nand your patience"},{"time":741422,"text":"in listening to me this afternoon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743104,"text":"Thank you, and Godspeed."}]}]}